title: Week 8 prep football games to watch
text:
Week 8 prep football games to watch Oct. 8, 2015 The Duffel Bag 
Homestead (5-2, 4-1 North Shore) at Whitefish Bay (6-1, 5-0), 7 p.m. Friday: The Blue Dukes can clinch a share of the North Shore title with a victory, or Homestead could set up a three-way tie for first that would include Cedarburg with one week to go. 
Brookfield Academy (6-1, 4-1 Midwest Classic) at Lake Country Lutheran (6-1, 5-0), 7 p.m. Friday: Lutheran can clinch a Midwest Classic Conference or division title for the fourth time in five seasons. 
Marquette (5-2, 4-1 Greater Metro) at Brookfield East (6-1, 4-1), 7 p.m. Friday: The challenge for any squad that faces East is putting points on the board. The Spartans recorded their fourth shutout of the season last week. Note that this game was originally scheduled for Thursday but will be played Friday. 
Milwaukee Washington vs. Milwaukee Morse-Marshall at Custer Stadium, 7:30 p.m. Friday: The battle for second in the Blackbourn Division features Washington, which has won four of its last five games, and Marshall, a winner of four in a row. 
Badger (5-2, 4-1 Southern Lakes) at Union Grove (5-2, 3-2) 7 p.m. Friday: The Badgers are a week away from a showdown for the conference title with Waterford, but first they must take care of business on the road. 
Greendale (5-2, 5-0 Woodland West) at Whitnall (5-2, 4-1 Woodland East), 7 p.m. Friday: Greendale goes for its 19th straight Woodland victory against a Falcons squad that won a share of the East Division title despite its loss to Greenfield last week. 
New Berlin Eisenhower (6-1, 4-1 Woodland West) at Greenfield (6-1, 4-1 Woodland East), 7 p.m. Friday: The East Division champion and the West Division runner-up have one common opponent: Pius XI. Eisenhower beat the Popes, 47-14, in Week 5; Greenfield defeated them, 26-22, in Week 2. 
Mark Stewart
